    "actions_taken": [
      "Crane boom set in boom rest",
      "Crane placed out of service",
      "BSEE onsite investigation conducted February 26, 2024",
      "Witness interviews conducted",
      "Incident area inspected"
    ],
    "summary": "On February 25, 2024, at approximately 0930 hours, a crane boom was damaged while attempting to raise the elevation of an I-beam approximately 1-inch on the Talos ERT LLC SM 130 B Facility. After unsuccessful attempts with come along winches, the contract construction crew attached the main line of the crane to the I-beam and applied tension up to 30,000 lbs. The crane boom was damaged at the heel section and a boom lattice after the load rating was exceeded. The crane was at a 55-degree angle with a maximum capacity of 21,500 lbs. There were no injuries and estimated repair cost is $400,000.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Ensure crane operators monitor weight indicators while having knowledge of maximum capacity of boom angle",
      "Do not connect cranes to or use to lift fixed objects",
      "Ensure JSEA discusses all hazards involved with planned operations",
      "Conduct stop work when original plan changes or is unsuccessful",
      "Adhere to API RP 2D standards as referenced in 30 CFR 250.198"
    ],
